    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-17T04:10:42+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-17T04:10:42+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T18:40:42Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-16T18:40:42Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred over the Tasman Sea extends a ridge over eastern parts of SA. A low pressure system south of the Bight will remain slow-moving until later Thursday when it will move southeastwards. An associated cold front will move across SA today followed by a second front later Thursday and Friday. A high pressure system will move across from the west over the weekend.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW009" description="Flinders" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain, most likely during this afternoon and evening. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds north to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h tending north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon and evening. Daytime maximum temperatures between 18 and 23.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely in the early morning. Winds northwesterly 25 to 40 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Winds west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h tending west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog west of the ranges. Slight chance of a shower. Light winds becoming south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 12 and 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
